reviewText: I'm sure happy this was on Amazon prime.  It is a great feel good movie, of a young troubled man (lost his father) ...finding himself, learning what a man is, and opening his heart for the first time.  Most of the movie takes place on the river and there is beautiful lessons that he learned.  This movie touched me so much I cried, in a good way.  I'd watch this again on day.  Great movie for young teens and adults.  I now want to take a ride on a river myself for a few days.  Loved this movie, especially as it progresses.
summary: A story of growing up and finding yourself.  Great!

reviewText: I would say this is an inspiring story of an outcast 'Loner', 'Loser' who finds his roots and the meaning of life on the River. Good clean fun, only because of the slightly silly kidnapping part did it not get 5 stars. The value lesson learned from the aspect of peer pressure and bullying is well worth viewing this movie. I found that I went back and watched several segments, particularly the beginning several times to get a better feel for what exactly happened.
summary: Great modern story of that special time when you find out the value of experience...

reviewText: This movie depicted a coming of age  story about a troubled teen who is still haunted by his fathers unexpected death. His grandfather, who is also the local sheriff, tries to give him fatherly advice which he doesn't accept. The sheriff does however talk him into taking a trek down a local river for 60 miles. This offers him many adventures as well as life lessons about himself. This is an excellent story and is well acted.
